uest for a new marriage license and certificate, confidential marriage license and certificate, or for a new birth certificate for any child of the petitioner.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;">(b) (1) A certified copy of the judgment of the court issued pursuant to this section shall, within 30 days, be filed by the petitioner with the Secretary of State.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 1em;">(2) A certified copy of the judgment of the court issued pursuant to this section shall, within 30 days, be filed by the petitioner with the State Registrar, if any of the following conditions are met:</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(A) The judgment includes an order for a new birth certificate and the petitioner has a birth certificate issued by this state.</div><div style="margin:0 0 1em 0;margin-left: 2.5em;">(B) The
